cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a method for improving visual classification accuracy, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves joint learning of a classifier and a generative stochastic translation network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a quadruplet loss suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper performs experiments on multiple datasets, indicating a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
